title: [Dabbings Mews, Mews Lane]
description: A long, straight avenue stretches north and south, bordered by a row of buildings on the west side.  On the east, a tall wall flanks the lane, carved stone figures set along its top.  A frosty breeze gusts down the road, the wind using the clear open straightaway to gain momentum.
paths: Obvious paths: northeast, south, southwest, west, northwest
